{"id": 5197, "title": "Ticket #5197: MSI installer doesn't set desktop policy when asked to", "description": "<blockquote>\nA user reports that the Windows installer asks whether it should set a desktop policy or a no-preemption policy, but it doesn't actually set a desktop policy when asked to.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2015-Aug-04 17:05:21 by tannenba:</em> <br/>\n\nFor an incident report on this problem, take a look at\n<a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www-auth.cs.wisc.edu/lists/htcondor-users/2015-July/msg00116.shtml\">this htcondor-users post</a>.\n\n<p></p><hr/>\n<em>2015-Aug-05 16:33:19 by johnkn:</em> <br/>\n\nFrom my testing, it looks like the MSI installer does set the START &amp; CONTINUE knobs, but it does not set SUSPEND or PREEMPT.  It also does not set <code>use policy : desktop</code></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Aug-12 16:43</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/1f66f785a341191d0862cd0167927daf25bf844d\">[45596]</a></span>: minor edit of 8.2.9 version history item <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5197\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5197'); return false;\" title=\"MSI installer doesn't set desktop policy when asked to\">#5197</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Aug-12 12:43</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/03d5d51dfecd3eb1653543f7f78d8